Stevia has its roots in South America where certain indigenous tribes have used it as a sweetener for centuries. Currently,Stevia is being used in many countries around the world. In Japan,Stevia accounts for 40 of the sweeteners consumed. Most Stevia sodas also use sugar alcohol as such as erythritol to sweeten their product. Virgil's contains Zero sugar alcohol.
